{"id": "EUVD-2025-13088", "enisaUuid": "4882c6f8-47c4-363a-8a02-ec01cbb86aac", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nmedia: venus: hfi: add check to handle incorrect queue size\n\nqsize represents size of shared queued between driver and video\nfirmware. Firmware can modify this value to an invalid large value. In\nsuch situation, empty_space will be bigger than the space actually\navailable. Since new_wr_idx is not checked, so the following code will\nresult in an OOB write.\n...\nqsize = qhdr->q_size\n\nif (wr_idx >= rd_idx)\n empty_space = qsize - (wr_idx - rd_idx)\n....\nif (new_wr_idx < qsize) {\n memcpy(wr_ptr, packet, dwords << 2) --> OOB write\n\nAdd check to ensure qsize is within the allocated size while\nreading and writing packets into the queue.", "datePublished": "2025-05-01T15:31:41", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-05T18:14:25", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-23158", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/101a86619aab42bb61f2253bbf720121022eab86", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/40084302f639b3fe954398c5ba5ee556b7242b54", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/679424f8b31446f90080befd0300ea915485b096", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/69baf245b23e20efda0079238b27fc63ecf13de1", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/cf5f7bb4e0d786f4d9d50ae6b5963935eab71d75", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/edb89d69b1438681daaf5ca90aed3242df94cc96", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/1b86c1917e16bafbbb08ab90baaff533aa36c62d", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/a45957bcde529169188929816775a575de77d84f", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/32af5c1fdb9bc274f52ee0472d3b060b18e4aab4", "https://lists.debian.org/debian-lts-announce/2025/05/msg00030.html", "https://lists.debian.org/debian-lts-announce/2025/05/msg00045.html"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-23158", "GHSA-f6mg-77cc-c9pm"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "04dede32-6354-3392-aa93-b0c20ad67338", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product